<section style="margin-bottom:3rem;">
  <h2>Why People Are Buying Lume Whole Body Deodorant</h2>
  <p>Body odor isn't just an armpit problem. Many people deal with odor in other areas and traditional deodorants aren't designed for whole-body use. Lume became popular because it promises safe, effective odor control anywhere on the body.</p>
</section>

<div class="divider-gradient" style="margin-bottom:3rem;"></div>

<!-- 3. SOLUTION -->
<section style="margin-bottom:3rem;">
  <h2>What Is Lume Whole Body Deodorant?</h2>
  <p>Lume is an aluminum-free deodorant cream that uses mandelic acid to prevent odor-causing bacteria. It's marketed for use on underarms, feet, and other body areas. It went viral through aggressive podcast advertising and bold claims about 72-hour protection.</p>
  <p style="margin-top:1rem;display:flex;align-items:center;gap:.5rem;">
    <span style="font-size:.75rem;font-family:var(--font-sans);text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.1em;color:var(--muted-foreground);">Why it went viral:</span>
    <span style="color:var(--accent);font-size:.875rem;">Heavy podcast sponsorships and bold marketing claims</span>
  </p>
</section>

<div class="divider-gradient" style="margin-bottom:3rem;"></div>

<!-- 4. HOW TO USE -->
<section style="margin-bottom:3rem;">
  <h2>How to Use Lume Whole Body Deodorant</h2>
  <ol class="how-to-steps">
    <li class="how-to-step"><span class="step-number">1</span><span class="step-text">Apply a pea-sized amount to clean, dry skin in odor-prone areas</span></li>
    <li class="how-to-step"><span class="step-number">2</span><span class="step-text">Spread evenly and allow to absorb for 1–2 minutes before dressing</span></li>
    <li class="how-to-step"><span class="step-number">3</span><span class="step-text">Reapply as needed — Lume claims up to 72 hours but we found 12–24 hours more realistic</span></li>
    <li class="how-to-step"><span class="step-number">4</span><span class="step-text">Store at room temperature to maintain cream consistency</span></li>
  </ol>
</section>

<div class="divider-gradient" style="margin-bottom:3rem;"></div>

